    "beneficiaries": [],
    "blacklists": [],
    "body": "I have two proposals to decrease the amount of influence top witnesses gain each day:\n1) Implement a tier system, in place of the current winner-take-all system:\n   * The top 20 witnesses get a fixed percentage of rounds (let's say 50% to be generous).  The 20th slot no longer rotates among the remaining witnesses, but instead among the top 20.\n   * The top 21-50th witnesses get a smaller percentage, lets say 25% of rounds.  This could be randomly divided among these 30 folks, so each round allocated to them would be divided among 19 of these witnesses.\n   * The remaining 51-100+ witnesses would get the remaining 25% of votes (or it could be divided up even more fine-grained).   The same system would be used where 19 of them will witness when this slot is allocated a round.  \n        * Of course there are top 100 witnesses who don't run active nodes, but a git proposal is in place to address that, by removing them from the witness queue if they've been missing blocks until they update their signing key.\n2) 90% (or some amount adjusted for the exchange value of Steem) of top 19 witness' blocks go unrewarded.  Instead of getting 1300 or however many SP a day, they'd only get 130, and the rest of their blocks would give them 0 monetary reward.  At current prices this would be enough for them to live off of and not have to do any other work than contribute to the Steem platform, but not cause them to overtake all active accounts in terms of vote weight.  As statisticians commonly say: \"there's no such thing as a free lunch\" (TINSTAAFL).",
